<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="118" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="118">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Thalpomys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thalpomys lasiotis" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lasiotis">Thalpomys lasiotis</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Cerrado, and has been recorded in the Brazilian states of Bahia, Minas Gerais, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Rondônia">Rondonia</normalizedToken>
, and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo, and in the Distrito Federal (
<bibRefCitation author="Hershkovitz, P" pageId="36" pageNumber="141" url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222939000770531" year="1990 a">Hershkovitz 1990a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation pageId="13" pageNumber="118">Ribeiro et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro, R" pageId="40" pageNumber="145" url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13364-011-0026-0" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rocha, CR" pageId="40" pageNumber="145" url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.mambio.2011.06.006" year="2011 a">Rocha et al. 2011a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation pageId="13" pageNumber="118">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pardiñas">Pardinas</normalizedToken>
and Teta 2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="118" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="118">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="118">
The red list of the IUCN ver 3.1 assigned the category &quot;Least Concern&quot; to 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Thalpomys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thalpomys lasiotis" order="Rodentia" pageId="13" pageNumber="118" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lasiotis">Thalpomys lasiotis</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Marinho Filho, J" pageId="36" pageNumber="141" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/21695/0" year="2016 b">Marinho-Filho et al. 2016b</bibRefCitation>
). The species appears in the official list of threatened species of Brazil with the category 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Endangered”">&quot;Endangered&quot;</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Iack-Ximenes, GE" pageId="36" pageNumber="141" url="http://www.icmbio.gov.br/portal/images/stories/comunicacao/publicacoes/publicacoes-diversas/dcom_sumario_executivo_livro_vermelho_ed_2016.pdf" year="2016">ICMBIO-MMA 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
